---
const workflowSteps = [
  "Raw content",
  "AI-assisted planning",
  "Course outline",
  "Lesson scripts",
  "Worksheets and quizzes",
  "Learner support assets",
  "Launch checklist"
];
---

<section class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-white border-b border-brand-border">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-16">

      <div class="lg:w-1/2 order-2 lg:order-1 relative w-full h-[400px]">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-brand-softBg rounded-3xl border border-brand-border shadow-inner p-8 overflow-hidden flex flex-col justify-center">

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 relative z-10">
                {workflowSteps.map((step, index) => (
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 bg-white p-3 rounded-lg border border-brand-border shadow-sm transform transition-transform hover:scale-[1.02]">
                        <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-brand-softBlue flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-brand-primary flex-shrink-0">
                            {index + 1}
                        </div>
                        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-textMain">{step}</span>
                        {index === 1 && (
                            <span class="ml-auto text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-brand-accent bg-brand-softGreen px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full border border-brand-accent/30">Speed</span>
                        )}
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>

            <!-- Connecting line behind items -->
            <div class="absolute left-[2.35rem] top-12 bottom-12 w-0.5 bg-brand-border z-0"></div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:w-1/2 order-1 lg:order-2">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-6 leading-tight">
          AI Support That Speeds Up Course Production
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-brand-textMuted mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          TheEduAssist uses AI-assisted workflows to support planning, organizing, repurposing, and improving learning content. AI helps speed up the process, while the final structure, learning experience, and strategy stay human-led.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-brand-softBlue p-6 rounded-xl border border-brand-primary/10">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-brand-primary mb-2 flex items-center">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2 text-brand-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" /></svg>
                Why AI-Assisted?
            </h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-brand-textMain leading-relaxed">
                We don't rely on fully automated course generators that produce generic content. We use AI as a powerful assistant to help our instructional designers structure your unique knowledge faster and more effectively.
            </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
